Part of what makes Lisp distinctive is that it is designed to evolve. As new abstractions become popular
(object-oriented programming, for example), it always turns out to be easy to implement them in Lisp. Like DNA, 
such a language does not go out of style.
                                         ------Paul Graham, ANSI Common Lisp
 
 
